        {{content.titles.accessibility}}
    </h1>

    <p>
        This site is committed to providing an experience that functions for the widest possible audience, regardless of technology or ability. It strives to conform to level <a rel="external noopener" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20/"><span aria-label="Double A">AA</span> compliance for the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (<abbr>WCAG</abbr>) 2<span aria-label="Dot">.</span>0</a>—guidelines explain how to make web content easier to use for people with disabilities.
    </p>
    <p>
        The code powering this site is <a href="https://www.w3.org/standards/">standards-compliant <abbr title="Hyper Text Markup Language">HTML</abbr>, <abbr title="Cascading Style Sheets">CSS</abbr>, and Java&#8202;Script</a>. Any person using a browser—past, present, or future—that honors these standards should be capable of navigating this site.
    </p>
    <p>
        In addition to being tested on modern browsers, both <a rel="external noopener" href="http://www.apple.com/accessibility/osx/voiceover/">mac&#8202;OS Voice&#8202;Over</a> and <a rel="external noopener" href="http://www.nvaccess.org/">NV Access's <abbr title="NonVisual Desktop Access">NVDA</abbr></a> have been used to test this site for ease of use with a screen reader. It has also been audited using <a rel="external noopener" href="http://wave.webaim.org/about"><abbr title="Web Accessibility Evaluation Tool">WAVE</a>, as well as the <a rel="external noopener" href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/accessibility-developer-t/fpkknkljclfencbdbgkenhalefipecmb">Chrome</a>, and <a rel="external noopener" href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/axe/lhdoppojpmngadmnindnejefpokejbdd">The <abbr title="Accessibility Engine">aXe</abbr></a> developer testing tool extensions.
    </p>
    <p>
        Issues with the site's accessibility can be submitted as a <a rel="external noopener" href="https://github.com/ericwbailey/ericbailey.design/issues">Git&#8202;Hub issue</a>, or by <a rel="external noopener" href="">emailing me directly</a>. I take these issues very seriously and will try to remedy the problem as quickly as time allows.
    </p>
    <p>
        Although I cannot guarantee that all content linked to or embedded by this site is fully accessible, I try to choose sites and services that embrace inclusive design principles.
    </p>

